{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ConvexPolygonShape2D","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot20ConvexPolygonShape2DC","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ConvexPolygonShape2D","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"ConvexPolygonShape2D","roleHeading":"Class"},"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritsFrom","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Shape2D"],"title":"Inherits From","kind":"relationships"},{"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GodotObject","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SQ","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SH","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s12IdentifiableP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantRepresentable","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantStorable"]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D\/points"]},{"title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D\/setPointCloud(_:)"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D\/godotClassName"],"title":"Type Properties"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A 2D convex polygon shape used for physics collision.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/convexpolygonshape2d"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ConvexPolygonShape2D"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A 2D convex polygon shape, intended for use in physics. Used internally in "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CollisionPolygon2D","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" when it’s in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CollisionPolygon2D\/BuildMode\/buildSolids"},{"type":"text","text":" mode."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"solid"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", which means it detects collisions from objects that are fully inside it, unlike "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConcavePolygonShape2D"},{"text":" which is hollow. This makes it more suitable for both detection and physics.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Convex decomposition:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" A concave polygon can be split up into several convex polygons. This allows dynamic physics bodies to have complex concave collisions (at a performance cost) and can be achieved by using several "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" nodes or by using the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CollisionPolygon2D"},{"text":" node in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CollisionPolygon2D\/BuildMode\/buildSolids"},{"text":" mode. To generate a collision polygon from a sprite, select the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Sprite2D","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" node, go to the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Sprite2D"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" menu that appears above the viewport, and choose "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create Polygon2D Sibling","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Performance:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is faster to check collisions against compared to "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConcavePolygonShape2D","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", but it is slower than primitive collision shapes such as "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CircleShape2D"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RectangleShape2D","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Its use should generally be limited to medium-sized objects that cannot have their collision accurately represented by primitive shapes."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/VariantRepresentable":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"VariantRepresentable","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VariantRepresentable"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Types that conform to VariantRepresentable can be stored directly in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Variant"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with no conversion.  These include all of the Variant types from Godot (for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example ","type":"text"},{"code":"GString","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Rect"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"Plane","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"), Godot objects (those that subclass","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"SwiftGodot.Object) as well as the built-in Swift types UInt8, Int64 and Double."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariantRepresentable","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantRepresentable","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/variantrepresentable"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/ConvexPolygonShape2D/points":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape2D\/points","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/convexpolygonshape2d\/points","title":"points","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"points","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot18PackedVector2ArrayC","text":"PackedVector2Array","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The polygon’s list of vertices that form a convex hull. Can be in either clockwise or counterclockwise order."}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/RectangleShape2D":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","title":"RectangleShape2D","abstract":[{"text":"A 2D rectangle shape used for physics collision.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"RectangleShape2D","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RectangleShape2D","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"RectangleShape2D","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/rectangleshape2d"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/ConvexPolygonShape2D/godotClassName":{"role":"symbol","title":"godotClassName","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"